  <title translate="true">combined UVE</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">A loop system&apos;s </text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;" translate="true">combined UVE </text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">is a weighted average of the horizontal and vertical UVEs,</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;" translate="true">UVE = (2 · nH · UveH + nV · UveV) / (2 · nH + nV),</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">where nH and nV are the loop counts for the horizontal and vertical dimensions. &#160;It serves as the sorting criterion for items displayed in the Geometry page&apos;s &quot;Loop Systems&quot; list box. See </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Statistical_Formulas" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">Statistical Formulas</link><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">.</text></para>
  </body>
